      @NotNull @Contract(value="_ -> new", pure=true) public @NotNull String join(String s)
      The join() method creates and returns a new string by concatenating all of the elements in an array (or an array-like object), separated by commas or a specified separator string. If the array has only one item, then that item will be returned without using the separator.
      https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/join
      定義:
      join インタフェース内 ICollectionList<V>
      パラメータ:
      s - Specifies a string to separate each pair of adjacent elements of the array. The separator is converted to a string if necessary. If omitted, the array elements are separated with a comma (","). If separator is an empty string, all elements are joined without any characters in between them.
      戻り値:
      The string conversions of all array elements are joined into one string.
      If an element is null or an empty array [], it is converted to an empty string.
